    <string name="help">Help</string>
    <string name="help_lora">When LoRa is enabled, the ELOC reports detections and regular heartbeats over long-range radio (LoRaWAN / The Things Network), independent of cell coverage.\n\nRegion — the LoRaWAN frequency plan configured on the device.\n\nUplink Interval — how often the device sends a status message. Shorter intervals give fresher data but use more power.</string>
    <string name="help_scheduler">The scheduler duty-cycles the recorder to save power: the ELOC stays awake (recording/detecting) for the awake duration, then sleeps for the sleep duration, and repeats.\n\nAwake Duration — how long the device runs in each cycle.\n\nSleep Duration — how long it sleeps between cycles.</string>
    <string name="help_intruder">Intruder detection uses the built-in accelerometer to sense when the device is being moved, shaken or taken down, and records the event.\n\nThreshold — how much movement is needed to count as an intruder event.\n\nDetection Window — the time window (in milliseconds) over which the movement is evaluated.</string>
